ong><hr>Simple solution: item with a focus effect and BRD listed? Slap on an inst mod, as well.<br>
<br>
Ya, I know. Too easy.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--> I don't agree with this line of reasoning. There are focus effects that hybrids can get that do very little to nothing for their class, yet they are listed on the classes usable. For example, a paladin has no use for a detrimental haste focus effect, nor a detrimental dot duration focus effect, nor any direct damage focus effects outside of the magic based one. Conversely, a shadowknight has no use for beneficial duration focus effects, beneficial distance focus effects, cold dot focus effects, and others.<br>
<br>
Not every item that has bard on it and has a focus effect necessarily means that a bard needs an instrument mod on it as well. However, the availability of specific mods should be similar to that of any other hybrid classes' availability for their mods. So if a paladin has 1-2 options for their top-most healing focus effect, then a bard should have 1-2 options for their highest mod. (for example 1-2 items with a 2.5-2.7 mod to brass). I've tried to give that many options with gates worn mods, where at least one item, if not more, from each zone had a worn mod on it. I'm somewhat content with the amount of worn mods overall in Gates. <p>-Zajeer</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#deddbf><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://p201.ezboard.com/btheconcerthall.showUserPublicProfile?gid=granart>Granart</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 27<br> <font color=#330000>(6/10/04 7:34 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://p201.ezboard.com/ftheconcerthallbackstage.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=19480.topic&index=23>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: um ok this is the right idea, SOE</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>paladin has 1-2 options for their <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>top-most</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> <hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--> thats -one- fundemental flaw since I guess that would be instruments for bards. And ever thought of why so many bards use their epic compared to say cleric that only need to equip it when they need to rez for example?<br>
